Looks nice enough. But you are doing conventions wrong. Read some java tutorials

The files need to be indented by the brackets and generally in Java it goes:

public class blah { (Bracket on same line now next Palidino was just a moron)
[Tab] void blarg() {
[tab][tab]
[tab]}
}

@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“glestrts, post:4, topic:361848”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=458122.msg3353331#msg3353331 date=1285542974]
winterLove == winterLove. Basically, you can shine it up, and modify it as you will, but it will always be a winterLove base. (And in my opinion, a very poorly made server.)
[/quote]
Its not poorly made, it just has features that are poorly implemented, If you consider what it was made for, then it was a success. The original ‘flight around runescape’ fullfilled its purpose. It was mainly after half-assed content was added, and then half-assed content on top of that that winterlove started to suck.

Basically winterlove isn’t as bad as most people make it out to be, its just that sources that circumvent the problems and contribute to the problems are very common.[/quote]

Yes, that’s what I meant to convey. I worded my response very poorly.
